Now, Hudson Executive is adding individuals with unusual experiences. Ms. Schapiro served as the first S.E.C. chairwoman during the Obama administration, overseeing moves like a lawsuit against Goldman Sachs over a mortgage-related investment created during the debt boom. In 2013, she joined the Promontory Financial Group, a bank consulting firm often criticized for its work in helping clients negotiate regulatory hurdles. She left as a full-time employee after less than a year.Ms. Schapiro is also a director at General Electric.Mr. Kovacevich led Wells Fargo during the financial crisis, watching as many of its competitors struggled. It was under him that the bank agreed to buy Wachovia in 2008 for $15.1 billion to bolster its nationwide presence. He left the bank in 2010.“We are pleased to add Dick Kovacevich and Mary Schapiro to our team and look forward to working with them and all of our Advisory Partners to generate investment opportunities and returns through Constructive Engagement,” Mr. Braunstein said in a statement.
Continue reading the main story






